titleNullable: Los Angeles 1992 Riot Deaths from LA Times
subtitleNullable: Data provide by the LA times regarding deaths related to the 1992 riots
descriptionNullable:
### Source

[latimes.com](https://spreadsheets.latimes.com/la-riots-deaths/)

#### Context

The [1992 LA Riots](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1992_Los_Angeles_riots) took places as a result of the [LAPD beating](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Los_Angeles_Police_Department#Controversies_and_misconduct) during the arrest of [Rodney King](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rodney_King). They were acquitted at trial by a jury. The riots began the day the verdicts were announced.


### Content

What's inside is more than just rows and columns. Make it easy for others to get started by describing how you acquired the data and what time period it represents, too.

### Acknowledgements
This data was published by the [LA Times here](https://spreadsheets.latimes.com/la-riots-deaths/). 

### Inspiration

Please be thoughtful and respectful of how you use this data.
